From 93569f42ebb00ebea634cdf33d666810ea9b458d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 17:16:31 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 32/44] inline-3d(#625): refresh the off-axis views every frame
 (the real mono-fallback cause)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The inline-3d session was permanently stuck on its mono fallback — one view,
eye "none", at the origin — so a rendered scene showed no cube (z=0 content
sits exactly at the camera and is clipped) and no look-around.

UpdateInlineView() holds BOTH the async eye pull and the 2-view gate, but it
is only reached from UpdateViews() (device-driven, never fires for a
sensorless inline session) or a canvas/render-state change. So the eye pull
ran once at setup, the gate was evaluated once (necessarily before any eyes
existed: eyes_valid=0 info=0) and NEVER revisited. Tracked eyes arriving
milliseconds later were delivered correctly and then ignored forever.

Drive it from XRSession::OnFrame's inline-3d branch — that early-returning
shortcut IS this session type's per-frame path (it runs the page's rAF and
ReportInline3DRects; there is no base layer / frame transport, so the normal
machinery below is skipped). Refresh before the callbacks so this frame's
getViewerPose() sees fresh views. This is exactly what UpdateInlineView's own
contract assumes ("kick off the async eye pull for the next frame and build
this frame from the latest cached eyes").

Instrumented evidence (tag+31 diag): the eye feed was healthy end to end —
GPU "GPU->browser eyes: bound=1 n=6 valid=1", browser "browser cached GPU
eyes: n=6 valid=1" — while the renderer's gate logged exactly ONCE with
eyes_valid=0 info=0. That one-shot log is what exposed the missing per-frame
drive; UpdatePresentationFrameState (tried first) is not on the inline-3d
path at all.
---
 third_party/blink/renderer/modules/xr/xr_session.cc | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/xr/xr_session.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/xr/xr_session.cc
index 08eeaf98d6c0e..db718f01ace91 100644
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/xr/xr_session.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/modules/xr/xr_session.cc
@@ -2247,6 +2247,18 @@ void XRSession::OnFrame(double timestamp,
       if (visibility_state_ == XRVisibilityState::HIDDEN) {
         return;
       }
+      // Refresh the off-axis views BEFORE the page's rAF runs, so this frame's
+      // getViewerPose() sees views built from the latest tracked eyes (and the
+      // pull for the next frame is kicked off). This shortcut IS the inline-3d
+      // frame path — UpdateInlineView is otherwise only reached from
+      // UpdateViews (device-driven, never for a sensorless inline session) or a
+      // canvas/render-state change, so the eye pull fired exactly once, at
+      // setup, before any eyes existed; the 2-view gate was evaluated once with
+      // eyes_valid=0 and never revisited, leaving the session pinned to its
+      // mono fallback (one view at the origin => z=0 scene content sits at the
+      // camera and is clipped, and no look-around) no matter that tracked eyes
+      // arrived milliseconds later.
+      UpdateInlineView();
       CHECK(animation_frame_ == nullptr);
       animation_frame_ = CreatePresentationFrame(true);
       {
